              <div class="quotetitle">molo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I've re-read the first three books a number of times; Dune is stand-out amazing. The next two are meh. Taste in books isn't universal; to each their own, but those of us who 'suffered' through God Awful of Dune and then stopped, without reading Heretics/Chapterhouse, are missing out on 'more of the same, but different.'</div><br /><br />Funny. I think &quot;God Emperor of Dune&quot; is easily the best book in the series. It's the only one I occasionally will re-read.</div><br /><br />I wouldn't go so far as to say that it's the &quot;best&quot;, but <span style="font-style: italic">God Emperor of Dune</span> is my favorite of the series.<br /><br />I concede that it's less-accessible than the rest (especially compared to <span style="font-style: italic">Dune</span>), though.

              

              
              
