              <div class="quotetitle">Twelve wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">CmdrPage wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Arthur C. Clarke wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic.</div><br />This applies to its use as a plot device as well.</div><br />If, in the story, anyone could learn to do it, it's technology.  If some people can do it but others can't, no matter how much they learn or try, it's magic.</div><br /><br />Then the &quot;Ancient gene&quot; mechanic that allows only certain people to use certain artifacts of Ancient technology would make Stargate fantasy?<br /><br />How is that so different from &quot;he's the Chosen one (or one of the Chosen) just because&quot; mechanic in lots of fantasy?<br /><br />Also note Ascension/etc.

              

              
              
