        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Meh. Parsing based on the distinction between technology and magic, the narrative type, mechanics, whatever, is just silly. What it basically amounts to is whether a book &quot;feels&quot; like science fiction or &quot;feels&quot; like fantasy — or whether the author or publisher doesn't want it to be classified as either. Genres are stupid for this exact reason. <br /><br />Margaret Atwood writes some fantastic science-fiction-like stories, but she insists she doesn't write science fiction (and was quoted as specifying martians, teleporters, and intergalactic space travel as particular qualities of sci-fi). Instead, she says she writes &quot;speculative fiction.&quot; It gets her on the &quot;literary fiction&quot; bookshelves in the stores anyway. But there's no reason someone who browses the sci-fi section shouldn't give her the same chance as someone who browses the literary fiction section. This is just one example.<br /><br />Genres suck.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
